synopsis: "Fuwa Olympic Tour" Beijing Taiwan version, a total of 100 episodes, each episode is 11 minutes, is by far the largest cartoon featuring the Olympic mascot as the main character. On the day of his 8th birthday, his father and mother gave him a set of Olympic mascot "Fuwa" as a gift. From this day, a lot of interesting things happened between "Fuwa" and Datoo's original "Kaku" toys. story. Through these stories, the origin and development of Olympic sports, the formulation and improvement of rules, and the amazing classic stories in the history of the Olympics are shown. (translated from douban)

title: Fuwa Wu Lianhuan
synopsis: The colorful fireworks that successfully bid for the 2008 Beijing Olympics awakened the five sleeping dragons in the Olympic Museum. They instantly transformed into five cute and spiritual children. Why did they come and why did they go? CCTV will launch a 106-episode large-scale sports humor animation series in the near future, the Olympic Fuwa "Five Links" will lead the audience to find the mystery in a fun way through the time and space of the century-old Olympics. 　　Before China hosts the Olympics next year, CCTV cooperated with the Olympics to launch a series of cartoons such as the Olympic Fuwa "Five Links", using animation to promote some of the Olympic spirit and the significance of hosting the Olympics. The animation format is very popular in recent years, and it is very easy for children to accept. Interpretation and propaganda in the form of animation, popularizing Olympic knowledge and propagating the Olympic spirit may be very good for Chinese children and children, and they are very easy to accept. It is a kind of mood, a feeling. After Moscow voted, China won and China could host the Olympics. Then we thought that cartoons should contribute to the Olympics, so we thought of using five children, they Each has a personality, which happens to be the color of the Olympic rings, and their personality is also in line with that (color), and their skin color is even those five colors. I decided to shoot a lot of episodes and talk about Olympic knowledge and thoughts about the Olympics through these five kids Show our China's desire for the Olympics, and show Chinese culture and interesting things 　　Olympic Fuwa "Five Links" is jointly produced by the three parties invested by CCTV, Communication University of China, and Shanghai Huisiqi Multimedia Animation Co., Ltd. CCTV, elite colleges and universities, and powerful animation companies join forces to jointly explore the operation mode of the animation market. So, what is the reason that the Communication University of China, which focuses on exporting talents, has become one of the tripartite investors. As a school, the investment in the creation of such a feature-length series is mainly based on these considerations. First of all, as for the Olympics, it is such a world-renowned event that contains the entire human civilization and history and culture. A kind of spiritual culture advocated. Therefore, we hope that through such a cartoon form, we can show to children the Olympic spirit contained in the fun Olympic events. The second point is mainly to enable our professional teachers and students to be able to Through the creation of cartoons, we can get such a professional training, and at the same time can make teaching and creation better combine 　　Olympic Fuwa "Five Links" is the world's first cartoon based on Olympic culture and history and Olympic mascots. The idea and theme have been highly valued by the International Olympic Organizing Committee. In order to successfully complete this large-scale Olympic-themed animation series, Director Li Jie of the Creative Department of CCTV Animation Company led the entire creative team to work together and cooperate sincerely, from planning to production. After three years, after several revisions and several overthrows, it is finally time to meet everyone. 　　 Our company tries to do a good job in the mid-term production. It is also a contribution to the Olympics and a participation. We hope to use our technology and our animation production philosophy to reflect the Olympic spirit in the animation. 　　 Why did the ancient Olympics reward the winners with olive branches? Why must the torch be lit before the Olympics? The large-scale animation series, "Five Links" of the Olympic Fuwa, is just unfolding in these vivid and interesting Olympic stories. It interprets the 100-year Olympics from the perspective of children and with childlike innocence, and interprets the theme of the happy Olympics. The Olympics is coming, let us look forward to it with the happy Wufuwa!(translated from douban)

title: Toripuru Baka
synopsis: No synopsis information has been added to this title. Help improve our database by adding a synopsis here.
background:
"Triple Baka" is a popular denpa song by LamazeP. He also created the song's PV. The lyrics to "Triple Baka" are somewhat vague, but seem to talk about being "stupid" (a "baka") because you are "creative" and "pumped" and "[Forgetting] about all your obligations and duties". A common interpretation is that Miku has become obsessed with the internet, and doesn't think she has time for anything else; however, the song could also be about LamazeP himself.

After its release, the song proved popular on Nico Nico, and currently has over 775,000 views (entering the Hall of Fame) and numerous derivatives. However, the song's various reprints on YouTube are even more popular; one of them reached over 6,600,000 views before being deleted. "Triple Baka" is often one of the first songs viewed by new VOCALOID fans, and may be part of the reason that Akita Neru and Kasane Teto are commonly believed to be VOCALOIDs. However, Akita Neru is a derivative of Hatsune Miku, and Kasane Teto is an UTAU.

"Triple Baka" is featured on the album EXIT TUNES PRESENTS THE COMPLETE BEST OF Lamaze-P.

(Source: VOCALOID Synthesizer Wiki)
